text: hello everyone today
I'd like to inform you that AWS who have
customers can now use up to 5 000 ybca
capacity units wcu power bco
what uses wcu to calculate and control
the operating resources that are
required to run wealth rules rule groups
and web ACLs
previously the wife permitted a maximum
of 1500 wecu power web BCL customers who
needed more than 1500 W ECU for their
web-based sales needed to request manual
limit increases
as well as launched new features and
improved core product capabilities over
the past few years customers have asked
us to increase the wcu limit so that it
is easier for them to use these new
features without worrying about running
out of capacity
now customers can use up to 5000 wecu in
their web ACLS without the need to
request a limit increase
web ecos that use more than 1500 wcus
will incure an additional charge per
million request process for each 500 wcu
the web ACL uses beyond the default
allocation of 1500. in addition
you will be charged
0.30 dollars per million requests for
each additional 16 kilobytes analyzed
beyond the default body inspection limit
